-- TNK-BP to Invest $58 Million in Ukraine Filling Stations
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-11-08T11:28:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-08/tnk-bp-to-invest-58-million-in-ukraine-filling-stations.html
TNK-BP, the Russian crude producer
half-owned by  BP Plc (BP/) , will invest $58 million in developing a
network of filling stations in Ukraine this year and in 2013.  TNK-BP is doing 35 re-branding and reconstruction projects
in Ukraine, the company said in an e-mailed statement today.
Seventeen new facilities will start operating this year.  TNK-BP has 146 filling stations in Ukraine.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
